    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not really about expectations though. it feels deeper than that. it's like the actual essence of me is just... gone. there's nothing left to find. i feel like i'm just a shell carrying around a body that doesn't belong to anyone anymore. it's exhausting to keep pretending there's something inside to save.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
